abstract: The Toyota Motor Corporation reported income of 426.7 billion yen, or about $3.7 billion, due in part to strong American sales of its Camry sedan and the remodeled FJ Cruiser sport utility vehicle.
snippet: The Toyota Motor Corporation reported income of 426.7 billion yen, or about $3.7 billion, due in part to strong American sales of its Camry sedan and the remodeled FJ Cruiser sport utility vehicle.
lead_paragraph: TOKYO, Feb. 6 — The Toyota Motor Corporation, the world’s second-largest car maker, reported a 7.3 percent gain in profit in the most recent quarter on Tuesday, bolstered by strong American sales of its Camry sedan and the remodeled FJ Cruiser sport utility vehicle.

headline.main: Toyota Stays on Track with 7.3 Percent Gain in Quarter
headline.print_headline: Toyota Stays on Track with 7.3 Percent Gain in Quarter
